        class="text-body text-sm md:text-base font-sans leading-relaxed space-y-6"
      >
        <p>
          Determining someone's exact age is a deceptively simple mathematical
          challenge. Because months differ in duration (from 28 to 31 days) and
          leap years inject an extra day into February every four years, simply
          dividing the total number of milliseconds by a generic year duration
          leads to off-by-one errors. This <strong>exact age calculator</strong> is
          built using correct calendar-date math to accurately calculate years, months,
          and days, ensuring precise tracking.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink font-sans mt-8 mb-3">
          Zodiac and Astrological Boundary Determinations
        </h3>
        <p>
          This tool goes beyond basic years and months arithmetic by computing
          astrological alignments:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Western Zodiac Sun Signs:</strong> Automatically computed using
            standard solar cycle ranges, matching your date of birth to signs like
            Capricorn, Aries, or Scorpio.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Chinese Lunar Zodiac:</strong> Determined using historical data
            mappings for Chinese New Year start times. Standard generators calculate
            this using January 1 as the cutoff date, leading to incorrect calculations
            for users born in January or early February. This birthday calculator
            checks your exact birth date against the Chinese Lunar New Year boundaries
            to return the correct animal (such as Rat, Dragon, or Horse).
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink font-sans mt-8 mb-3">
          Understanding Leap Years in Date Math
        </h3>
        <p>
          A common bug in date arithmetic is the handling of leap days. The year
          2000 was a leap year, containing 366 days, while 2001 was not. If a
          person born on February 29, 2000, measures their age on February 28,
          2001, they are technically 364 days old. Since February 29 does not
          exist in 2001, standard systems must determine if the user turns one
          full year old on February 28 or March 1. This system uses calendar
          logic, completing the year boundary on the transition to March 1 in
          non-leap years.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink font-sans mt-8 mb-3">
          Privacy & Execution
        </h3>
        <p>
          None of your personal birth information is ever uploaded to a database
          or shared. All computations execute on your local device within the
          client browser window. You can freely model dates for historical
          queries or project future ages safe in the knowledge that your data
          remains 100% private.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink font-sans mt-8 mb-3">
          How Exact Age Calculations Handle Calendar Anomalies
        </h3>
        <p>
          Calculating age down to the day is a deceptively simple mathematical
          challenge due to calendar anomalies. Gregorian calendar months vary in
          length between 28, 29, 30, and 31 days. When calculating the
          difference between two dates—such as February 29 on a leap year and
          March 1 on a non-leap year—a standard difference calculation will
          yield slight variances. Our calculator uses a logical calendar
          subtraction algorithm that adjusts for the number of days in the
          preceding month, borrowing days when necessary to ensure the result
          matches standard legal and biological age metrics.
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink font-sans mt-8 mb-3">
          Legal Significance of Age Milestones Across Countries
        </h3>
        <p>
          Age calculation has significant legal implications globally,
          establishing boundaries for legal rights and responsibilities. The age
          of majority—the threshold where an individual is legally recognized as
          an adult—is set at 18 in most countries, though it is 19 in Alabama
          and Nebraska, and 21 in Mississippi. Other legal milestones include
          the age of consent, driving eligibility, voting rights, and the
          minimum age for purchasing alcohol or tobacco. Using an age calculator
          helps verify compliance with legal requirements for employment
          contracts and age-restricted transactions.
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink font-sans mt-8 mb-3">
          Chronological Age vs. Biological Age
        </h3>
        <p>
          While this tool calculates your chronological age—the exact duration
          since your birth date—scientists also track biological age. Biological
          age refers to the physiological wear and tear on your cells and
          organs. It is influenced by genetics, lifestyle habits, diet,
          exercise, and stress levels. While two individuals may share the exact
          same chronological age of 45, their biological ages could differ by
          over a decade. Biological age is measured using epigenetic biomarkers
          and DNA methylation tests.
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink font-sans mt-8 mb-3">
          Calculating Half-Birthday Milestones and Anniversaries
        </h3>
        <p>
          Many individuals track secondary milestones such as half-birthdays
          (exactly six months after your birth date) or the number of days lived
